du -h
file descriptors: 0=input, 1=output, 2=errors
I/O/error redirection (> / < / >>), /dev/null, 0,1,2 (&)
examples: 
	ls files.txt not-here 1>out 2>out.err
	ls files.txt not-here > out.both 2>&1
diff/sdiff/vimdiff
cut -d[delimiter] -f[number of field]
tr translates, for example: tr ":" " "
column -t for table format
scp / sftp
customize zsh prompt (export PROMPT or PS1 env variable in .zshrc)
ps [-e/-f/-u/-p/-H] , pstree
set $EDITOR=vim
bang to bring up commands from history - !^ / !$ / !:[N]
Ctrl-r reverse shell history search
dmesg -T | less
lsblk / lvmdiskscan / fdisk / mkfs / mkswap / swapon , make sure swap works and is in use!
nmtui / traceroute / tracepath / netstat / tcpdump / telnet to test port connectivity
setuid
!* to recall last used arguments
grep -Ev '^#|^$'

